						<summary>

						<p>VIJAYARANGA CHOKKANĀTHA.</p>						

						<p>SŌBHAKṚIT 1722 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription mentions the cyclic year Śōbhakṛit. The cyclic year Śōbhakṛit is fallen in the year Śaka 1643 and corresponding year 1772 A.D.</p>						

						<p>A singer <hi rend="italic">(pāṭakam)</hi> Vaidyappaya, the son of Venkatēśvara, an instructor <hi rend="italic">(śikshaka)</hi> of the <hi rend="italic">nāṭaka-śāla</hi> of Vijayaranga Chokkanātha nāyaka caused the construction of steps and <hi rend="italic">manḍapa</hi> to temple (?) of Jambukēśvaram.</p>						

						</summary>
